"{\"uid\": \"thefederalist.com-2024-08-01-why-non-christians-should-care-about-the-olympics-drag-show\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The drag spectacle creates doubt about some cherished assumptions of the modern secular world.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 94, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremonies of the Paris Olympics were deeply offensive to Christians around the world.\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 166, \"end\": 176, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9648419206141904, \"rank\": 0.036436950570867314, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Numerous people from across the denominational spectrum have described this event as blasphemous and even demonic.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, I would like to say something to the non-Christians who may be uneasy about the opening ceremonies but cannot quite explain why.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps the opening ceremony bothers you, but you are not quite ready to align yourself with its Christian critics.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 564, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 546, \"end\": 555, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9974901461639731, \"rank\": 0.0025161690524046, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let me help you with this.\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The group of people who created this spectacle betrayed the trust that was placed in them.\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were given responsibility for an event that should have honored the athletes and the pursuit of excellence.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 796, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, they used it to put themselves and their agenda at the center of attention.\", \"from\": 797, \"to\": 881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And their conduct creates doubt about some cherished assumptions of the modern secular world.\", \"from\": 882, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us start by giving a moment's thought to the athletes.\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1035, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These world-class athletes have spent years preparing for the opportunity to compete in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1036, \"to\": 1137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The athletes deserve to be honored for their dedication and pursuit of excellence.\", \"from\": 1138, \"to\": 1220, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, these men and women who are talented and self-disciplined were upstaged by men and women who are neither.\", \"from\": 1221, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not need to be a Christian to see that something is seriously wrong with this picture.\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1361, \"end\": 1370, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9974901461639731, \"rank\": 0.0025161690524046, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have all been told that we are supposed to tolerate and even honor the type of people who created this spectacle.\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1548, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gay people are oppressed victims, after all.\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were born this way, after all.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is nothing wrong with being gay, after all.\", \"from\": 1630, \"to\": 1679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can we agree that pathological self-centeredness is not \\\"virtually normal?\\\"\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Suppose we agree, for the sake of argument, that people are \\\"born gay,\\\" (a point I by no means concede).\", \"from\": 1757, \"to\": 1861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can we at least agree that wearing garish costumes is not an inborn, immutable trait?\", \"from\": 1862, \"to\": 1947, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can we agree that having an irresistible urge to ridicule other people's beliefs is not generally a sign of good mental health?\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if we agree that people do not \\\"choose to be gay,\\\" can we agree that these individuals did chose to put on this particularly tasteless display in a wildly inappropriate time and place?\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2266, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They did not make \\\"a choice\\\": They made hundreds of choices over the course of many years that led them to believe what they did was a fine thing to do.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2419, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The artistic \\\"genius\\\" who created this event claimed he wanted to be \\\"inclusive.\\\"\", \"from\": 2421, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He expects us to take this claim at face value.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He is either delusional about the effects his work would have, or he is lying through his teeth.\", \"from\": 2551, \"to\": 2647, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He knew perfectly well he would offend and disgust many people.\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2711, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He had to have known that even among the people who were not offended for religious reasons, a sizeable number would be bored, turn off their TV, and stop watching the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2712, \"to\": 2889, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Various individuals and entities associated with the Paris Olympics have issued statements with varying degrees of \\\"explanation\\\" and \\\"apology.\\\"\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not going to attempt to catalogue them.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3079, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not interested, and I will tell you why.\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their apologies are phony.\", \"from\": 3126, \"to\": 3152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These people are not the slightest bit sorry for offending 2.4 billion Christians around the world.\", \"from\": 3153, \"to\": 3252, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3224, \"end\": 3234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9648419206141904, \"rank\": 0.036436950570867314, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are not sorry for hogging the stage and detracting from people of authentic achievement.\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3346, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are sorry they got caught.\", \"from\": 3348, \"to\": 3379, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They'd do the same again if they thought they could get away with it.\", \"from\": 3380, \"to\": 3449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They feel entitled to do what they want for their own purposes.\", \"from\": 3450, \"to\": 3513, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have a vision for society.\", \"from\": 3514, \"to\": 3545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They believe they are entitled to offend and marginalize the people who stand in their way.\", \"from\": 3546, \"to\": 3637, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, it is an interesting question to ask: who is the relevant \\\"they\\\" here?\", \"from\": 3639, \"to\": 3714, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I make no claim to know exactly who is responsible for the opening ceremonies.\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3793, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But someone chose this particular gay man to be in charge.\", \"from\": 3794, \"to\": 3852, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone approved the end product.\", \"from\": 3853, \"to\": 3886, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Someone is issuing these \\\"apologies\\\" and \\\"explanations.\\\"\", \"from\": 3887, \"to\": 3943, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not know who these people are.\", \"from\": 3944, \"to\": 3979, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But we can make a general statement without fear of contradiction.\", \"from\": 3980, \"to\": 4046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whoever they are, they have the sanction of some very powerful people: the International Olympic Committee, corporate advertisers, and no doubt, the government of France.\", \"from\": 4048, \"to\": 4218, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4123, \"end\": 4154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 4211, \"end\": 4217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"score\": 0.8426538535441496, \"rank\": 0.15613758056093704, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Third_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The self-identified gays and drag queens are a long way from being \\\"victims.\\\"\", \"from\": 4219, \"to\": 4296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You may ask, why can not we just live and let live?\", \"from\": 4298, \"to\": 4349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Why can not we just tolerate each other?\", \"from\": 4350, \"to\": 4390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am sorry to have to inform you: the \\\"live and let live\\\" train left the station a long time ago.\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The people who put on this display have the sanction of the global ruling class.\", \"from\": 4490, \"to\": 4570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is who they are.\", \"from\": 4571, \"to\": 4592, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What the world witnessed in Paris gives us a glimpse of what they want.\", \"from\": 4593, \"to\": 4664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4621, \"end\": 4626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999981857038707, \"rank\": 1.8142992846524708e-06, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is their plan for you and your family.\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4708, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They think they are entitled to put themselves and their agenda at the center of anything they are in charge of.\", \"from\": 4709, \"to\": 4821, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They are entitled to offend you, and then expect you to go along with the pretense that they did not really mean it.\", \"from\": 4822, \"to\": 4938, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Each of us must decide whether this is what we want for ourselves and our families-and then think, and act, accordingly.\", \"from\": 4940, \"to\": 5060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not have to be a Christian to see that we should stop taking the gay radicals and their handlers at face value.\", \"from\": 5061, \"to\": 5179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5085, \"end\": 5094, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9974901461639731, \"rank\": 0.0025161690524046, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9 2026 The Federalist, A wholly independent division of FDRLST Media.\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"All rights reserved.\", \"from\": 5251, \"to\": 5271, \"entities\": []}]}"